  "interpretation": "Work-normalised variance-reduction ratios are an UPPER bound idealisation: the inner integrand here is the smooth 1-D Black-Scholes put, where Sobol-RQMC's O(N^-1) convergence yields a very large ratio at N_inner. Real nested valuations with payoff kinks and higher inner dimension will see SMALLER (but still material) RQMC gains - the recorded outer-basis precedents (Sobol 2.8x-7.1x) are the realistic operating range. CRN across the guarantee-on/off legs is dimension-robust; antithetic helps the smooth mean but not the extreme quantile (see tail_study)."
